  "body": "*Title*: *Allow specifying a different transport socket config for cluster health checks*\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\nIt is my understanding that today, cluster active health checking uses the [transport socket specified for the cluster](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/9521f88d93c1454739895d979e16000d1df0729b/api/envoy/api/v2/core/health_check.proto#L181). I'd like to allow overriding that transport socket for health checks. \r\n\r\nI have a use case where I need to proxy at L4, but I'd still like the power of L7 health checks. I'd like to allow specifying an optional healthcheck transport socket in a cluster's config. Adding this field in the cluster config makes it easy to add a new transport socket factory in upstream_impl.h that is used in Upstream::Host's createHealthCheckConnection if the optional field has been set.\r\n\r\nI see that there have been similar, unresolved Issues in the past, so I'm open to any other implementation suggestions.\r\n",
